In terms of logging in, the user could use their existing Google, Twitter, or Facebook account to create OAuth login. If they do not have those accounts, we can direct them to another page to create an account on the app using an email/phone number and new password. DUO Authentication could also play a role in improving security when logging in. They will enter their preferred location and set filters based on possible preferred cuisines (to show restaurants that fit the description nearby), and preferred modes of public transport (including bluebikes), and the system will return options that best fit the filters with the lowest crime rate possible.
